  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>It looks good.

Point 5 doesn't seem to be addressed at all.  I just flubbed the tarball
creation mission because the requirements are hard to parse in paragraph form
and I didn't read it carefully enough.

I'd change the requirements paragraph for the tarball extraction part to be this:

"""
Your mission is to:

* download the tarball
* unpack it
* find and upload the ghello-0.4/ghello.c file

Note that the tarball is following the conventions mentioned above by using a
wrapper directory.
"""

The requirements paragraph for the tarball creation part should be:

"""
Your mission is to:

* create a myproject-0.1 directory
* download the files above and place them in the directory
* in the parent directory, create a gzipped tarball of the myproject-0.1
directory called myproject-0.1.tar.gz
* upload your tarball
"""

That's much easier to parse.

Out of curiosity, are there reasons for keeping the requirements in paragraph
form?  Is it better in some way that I'm not thinking of?</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
